Ideas Explored
Brainstormed Ideas:
    1. Idea 1:
        ◦ Description: Executive Summary
          In today’s modern times, most households have both parents working which allows
          them very little time to closely monitor their children’s school progress. This
          situation further deteriorates with single-parent households. The eLearner
          application seeks to bridge this gap but offering a platform that will offer better
          communication channels between teachers and parents. The
          eLearner application seeks to change the current landscape of Lesotho’s primary
          education by offering tools that will enable parents and teachers to focus on key
          areas concerning their children’s educational needs.
          Our commitment to innovation is evident in the use of advanced analytics to
          pinpoint key focus areas regarding early childhood learning. The seamless
          integration of our platform with various software tools simplifies the process of
          obtaining meaningful information to enable schools, parents, and teachers to make
          sound decision regarding the academic trajectory of learners.
          The Product
          The eLearner application comes in the form of a web portal. This cloud-based
          solution will offer opportunities for parents to engage teachers on issues pertaining
          to learner academic progress, attendance, class participation and behavior,
          assignments to name but a few.
          Unlike other competitor products already in the market, the eLearner application
          focuses mainly on providing a tool or platform to improve school-to-home
          communication. Parents will gain access to meaningful insights that will aid them in
          tracking their children’s academic progress. Waiting for end of term reports has
          proved to be rather an inefficient way of tracking learner academic progress.
          Furthermore, the eLearner application will closely be aligned with the national
          school curriculum to ensure that learners focus on key modules. Practise quizzes
          and tests will be adapted to reflect normal day to day school learnings and
          academic growth. This adaptive approach will encourage a more outcome-based
          approach to learning.
          With full customization capabilities, participating schools will be able to submit
          tailor-made practice tests for their respective learners. eLearner will provide a full
          customizable platform to enable teachers to conduct practise tests and exercises.
          Our comprehensive test analysis reports will focus on two key aspects namely
          speed and accuracy. This will enable teachers and parents identify key areas of
          improvement. Learner test results will be analysed through machine learning i
          order to determine common cognitive patterns.
          With the increased rates of child kidnappings and abductions across the world,
          instant communication has become a necessity. Parents will receive notifications generated through the eLearner application. Furthermore, phase 2 of the pilot
          project will involve integration with tools like Whatsapp. This safety mechanism will
          ensure that parents are always up to date with regards to their children’s school
          affairs.
        ◦ In summary, the eLearner application will have the following features:

        ◦ Setup of school timetables and other school activities or events.
        ◦ Instant messaging and notifications.
        ◦ Setup of reminders/delayed messages.
        ◦ Setup of learner practice tests, quizzes, and homework exercises.
        ◦ Comprehensive assessment reports using artificial intelligence (AI).
        ◦ Time-bound learner speed tests
        ◦ Auto-assessment of learner progress using machine learning.
        ◦ Teacher-parent communication chats.
        ◦ Class attendance tracking.
        ◦ Translation abilities to Sesotho language.
