Selected MVP Concept
MVP Summary:
    • Project Name: eLearner
    • Description: A cloud-based web portal connecting parents and teachers for improved student progress monitoring
    • Problem Solved: Bridges communication gaps between parents and teachers
    • Target Audience: Parents, teachers, and school administrators
    • Key Features:
        ◦ Instant messaging and notifications
        ◦ Student progress reports with AI analytics
        ◦ Customizable quizzes and assessments
        ◦ Attendance tracking
        ◦ Curriculum-aligned practice tools
    • Expected Outcomes: Improved student outcomes, better communication, and enhanced parental involvement
Reasons for Selection:
    1. Feasibility: Builds on existing web technologies
    2. Innovation: Integrates AI for tailored insights
    3. Alignment: Directly addresses stakeholder needs
Challenges and Opportunities:
    • Challenges:
        ◦ Implementing machine learning for cognitive analysis
        ◦ Ensuring data security and privacy
        ◦ Adoption of new tools by teachers and parents
    • Opportunities:
        ◦ Scalability to other regions
        ◦ Potential for integration with additional educational tools
        ◦ Enhancement of national education standards

